The Iroquois lived up to its excellent reputation
The hotel is quite luxurious
Rooms are really well appointed with fantastic showers
very comfortable beds and enough space
Staff are friendly and helpful
It's situated in the heart of Manhattan with everything you would want just a stroll away
In particular you can
within minutes
be at Times Square for shows
dining
picking up a ride on a tour bus
Fifth Avenue shopping starts just round the corner and the Rockefeller Centre
Empire State
Grand Central
St Pat's Cathedral
etc are just a few blocks away
Local buses are good for Central Park and Bryant Park (2 blocks distance) is a great place to have coffee and relax
You can also pick up a Newark Liberty airport bus at corner of Bryant Park and Fifth Avenue
